      "role": "user",
      "content": "I get that, but when you're on the ground, does it not feel like the ethnic lines are the main thing? Like, if you look at most of the flashpoints or the way people organize locally, isn't it mostly just these tribes fighting over territory? I'm trying to see if it's realistic to just frame it as \"tribal conflict\" in my report, or if that's oversimplifying the nature of how these people actually behave.",
